64	            while endpoint:

60	    async def fetch_all_pages(self, endpoint):
61	        all_data = []  # To accumulate results from each page
62	        
63	        async with httpx.AsyncClient(headers=self.headers) as client:
64	            while endpoint:
65	                response = await client.get(endpoint)
66	                data = response.json()
67	                results = data['results']

61	        all_data = []  # To accumulate results from each page
62	        
63	        async with httpx.AsyncClient(headers=self.headers) as client:
64	            while endpoint:
65	                response = await client.get(endpoint)
66	                data = response.json()
67	                results = data['results']
68	                all_data.extend(results)  # Add results to the main list

60	    async def fetch_all_pages(self, endpoint):
61	        all_data = []  # To accumulate results from each page
62	        
63	        async with httpx.AsyncClient(headers=self.headers) as client:
64	            while endpoint:
65	                response = await client.get(endpoint)
66	                data = response.json()
67	                results = data['results']
68	                all_data.extend(results)  # Add results to the main list
69	                endpoint = data.get('next')  # Update to next page URL or None if at the end
70	        
71	        # Convert accumulated data to a DataFrame
72	        final_df = pd.DataFrame(all_data)
73	        
74	        print(final_df)

52	    "spouse-incomes": "https://www.courtlistener.com/api/rest/v4/spouse-incomes/",
53	    "alerts": "https://www.courtlistener.com/api/rest/v4/alerts/",

55	    "memberships": "https://www.courtlistener.com/api/rest/v4/memberships/",
56	    "citation-lookup": "https://www.courtlistener.com/api/rest/v4/citation-lookup/"
57	}
58	        
59	
60	    async def fetch_all_pages(self, endpoint):
61	        all_data = []  # To accumulate results from each page
62	        
63	        async with httpx.AsyncClient(headers=self.headers) as client:
64	            while endpoint:
65	                response = await client.get(endpoint)
66	                data = response.json()
67	                results = data['results']
68	                all_data.extend(results)  # Add results to the main list
69	                endpoint = data.get('next')  # Update to next page URL or None if at the end
70	        
71	        # Convert accumulated data to a DataFrame
72	        final_df = pd.DataFrame(all_data)
73	        
74	        print(final_df)
75	        return final_df
76

56	    "citation-lookup": "https://www.courtlistener.com/api/rest/v4/citation-lookup/"
57	}

59	
60	    async def fetch_all_pages(self, endpoint):
61	        all_data = []  # To accumulate results from each page
62	        
63	        async with httpx.AsyncClient(headers=self.headers) as client:
64	            while endpoint:
65	                response = await client.get(endpoint)
66	                data = response.json()
67	                results = data['results']
68	                all_data.extend(results)  # Add results to the main list
69	                endpoint = data.get('next')  # Update to next page URL or None if at the end
70	        
71	        # Convert accumulated data to a DataFrame
72	        final_df = pd.DataFrame(all_data)
73	        
74	        print(final_df)
75	        return final_df
76

169	        async with aiohttp.ClientSession(headers=self.headers) as session:

91	    def _get_did(self, path=''):
92	            '''
93	            Makes a unique device id from a random uuid (uuid.uuid4).
94	            if the pickle file doesn't exist, this func will generate a random 32 character hex string
95	            uuid and save it in a pickle file for future use. if the file already exists it will
96	            load the pickle file to reuse the did. Having a unique did appears to be very important
97	            for the MQTT web socket protocol
98	
99	            path: path to did.bin. For example _get_did('cache') will search for cache/did.bin instead.
100	
101	            :return: hex string of a 32 digit uuid
